    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-09-10T03:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-09-10T03:35:00-05:00" n="173"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d173">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.5018/7: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-09-10T12:00:00+03:25"
                            >September 10, 1942—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received September 10—11:54
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>287. Transport Board mentioned in my 271, August 26, has been organized and held
                    first meeting. It is headed by Ali Motamedi, young Iranian of good record and
                    reputation, and includes delegates for Police and Finance Departments. British
                    Legation is represented by its Commercial Secretary and this Legation by Minor,
                    both of whom will serve until suitable experts can be obtained. Committee
                    considers nationwide registration of motor vehicles in different categories is
                    necessary before it can proceed with tire and gasoline rationing or other
                    essential duties. It has requested authority of Council of Ministers to proceed
                    therewith without delay.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
